We will first need to align our assembled genome to a reference genome ( here: channel catfish).

### Alignment using LAST

#first create index of I. Punctatus
~/last-1133/src/lastdb -P4 -uNEAR -R01 Ch.catfish-NEAR Assembly.fasta                      

##Create matrice for substitution and gap frequencies between species
~/last-1133/scriptslast-train -P4 --revsym --matsym --gapsym -E0.05 -C2 Ch.catfish-NEAR ~/Genome/AncTri.Genome.Assembly.fasta > Ict-Anc.mat

##alignment with minimum 1MB length (-l 1000)
c
##testing
~/last-1133/scripts/last-train -P4 --revsym --matsym --gapsym -E0.05 -C2 Ch.catfish-NEAR ~/wengan/Anc_WenganD.2.SPolished.asm.wengan.fasta> Ict-Anc.test.mat

nice -n 19 ~/last-1133/src/lastal -m50 -E0.05 -C2 -p Ict-Anc.mat  Ch.catfish-NEAR  ~/Genome/AncTri.Genome.Assembly.fasta  ‑‑format=general:nmismatch,name1,strand1,start1,end1,name2,strand2,start2,end2,length1,length2 | ~/last-1133/src/last-split -m1 > ict-anc.test.1000.maf
